      • path

        public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> path
        All node of a graph has a number; path is an array which contains successively the number of nodes of the shortest path between the current soil cell and the destination soil cell(last target) (when a agent leave a node of the path, the next node is what I call next target or targetPoint_Umeter )

      • targetSoilCell

        public C_SoilCellGraphed targetSoilCell
        After building the path, targetSoilCell is successively the next node of the path.
        Agent is arrived at the next node if currentSoilCell == targetSoilCell.
        Agent is arrived at it's final destination when index Of path == length of path
        targetSoilCell is initialize by agent currentSoilCell
